  "prompt": "Can you be a pilot if you wear glasses?",
  "response": "Yes, you can be a pilot if you wear glasses. Many aviation authorities, including the Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) in the United States, allow pilots to wear corrective lenses such as glasses or contact lenses as long as their vision meets specific standards when corrected. Prospective pilots must pass a vision test during their medical examination to ensure their vision is within the acceptable limits for safe flying. There are different classes of medical certificates (Class 1, Class 2, and Class 3) with varying vision requirements depending on whether you plan to be a commercial pilot, an airline transport pilot, or a private pilot. If you meet the required vision standards with corrective lenses, you can pursue a career as a pilot.",
